			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	As a Senior Designer for the Verticals Marketplace, your job is to be an ambassador to the User Experience on eBay. By taking a proactive approach to designing rich prototypes through a thoughtful user-centric approach, you&nbsp;and your team will forge the way users shop on the site.</p>
<p>
	This is a seasoned role with the excitement to design for a business vertical end-to-end. The Buyer Experience Group leverages a cross-disciplinary suite of colleagues ranging from Program management to Development &amp; business. The Senior designer is the a key partner in helping visualize the business, the product experiences and proactively iterating on these models and simulations to move the product forward.</p>
<p>
	<strong>You&#39;ll be part of a design team that is responsible for:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Designing the interaction, layout, and visual look of experiences on eBay</li>
	<li>
		Creating wireframes and Photoshop mockups.</li>
	<li>
		Working with various stakeholders, from product managers to customer support, to the engineers who will convert your mockups into working pages.</li>
	<li>
		Proposing A/B tests, working with engineers to implement the tests and then evaluating the results.</li>
	<li>
		Conducting and/or participating in informal usability tests.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>You have:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		A demonstrated ability to turn complex challenges into simple and elegant design solutions.</li>
	<li>
		A passion for good user experience design.</li>
	<li>
		An empathic ability to place yourself in the role of the person you are designing for.</li>
	<li>
		Experience designing complex interfaces for the web.</li>
	<li>
		Skills demonstrating your understanding of typographical technique, layout principles, color theory, and web design standards.</li>
	<li>
		An understanding of modern HTML, CSS, and JavaScript techniques.</li>
	<li>
		Proficiency using Photoshop, Illustrator, and other industry standard design tools.</li>
	<li>
		Good communication and interpersonal skills, a sense of humor, and a desire to make the world a better place through exceptional design.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Bonus points for any of the following:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Experience or strong interest in data visualization or infographics.</li>
	<li>
		Previous experience in the automotive industry</li>
	<li>
		Mobile GUI Interface experience</li>
	<li>
		3+ Years agency experience</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Please provide an online portfolio&nbsp;&amp; case studies demonstrating your skills as a Design lead, Art Director and/or User Experience Designer for interactive media.</p>
<p>
	This position is located at eBay headquarters in San Jose, CA.&nbsp;</p>
